<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1202991>
    dc:description "FIGURE 19. Caligus asymmetricus Kabata, 1965, female.A, habitus, dorsal; B, antenna, post-antennal process and maxillule, drawn in situ; C, maxilliped; D, sternal furca; E, endopod of leg 2, showing denticulate ornamentation on lateral margin of second segment; F, exopod of leg 2; G, rami of leg 3, drawn in situ; H, leg 4. Scale bars: 1.0 mm on A, 200 µm on B, C, G, H, 100 µm onE, F, 50 µm on D." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1202991/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

